kb:design-system-shadcn a ktype:Feature;
    rdfs:label "Design System (shadcn-svelte)";
    kpred:feature-id "F79";
    kpred:part-of kb:design-system;
    kpred:honest-note "Split from kb:design-system (2026-07-12). One IRI was naming two different things: the visual design system (a ktype:Concept — fonts, colors, components) and the shadcn-svelte migration (a ktype:Feature). RDF merged them into one entity with two labels and two contradictory statuses.";
    kpred:has-status "scaffolded";
    kpred:description "shadcn-svelte foundation on Tailwind v4, themed to the Liquid aesthetic. Preflight (Tailwind's CSS reset) is deliberately omitted — src/lib/styles/tailwind.css imports only the theme and utilities layers, so global.css remains the visual source of truth and the app renders unchanged. Every shadcn token is a var() reference into global.css (e.g. --color-primary -> --accent teal); shadcn's neutral 'accent' hover slot is kept inside @theme only, never clobbering the Liquid --accent custom property. Starter components: button, badge, card, separator, skeleton under src/lib/components/ui/. Pilot: the About-footer 'Send feedback' button.";
    kpred:relates-to kb:rebrand-kb-to-graph;
    kpred:candidate "P1 Settings forms: unify the three settings pages' inputs/selects/switches on shadcn form controls — the largest consistency win.", "P2 Review cards: Card + color-coded status Badge (pending/confirmed/refined/rejected/superseded) across StatementCard, DiffEntry, AlignmentCard.", "P3 Loading states: Skeleton placeholders for graph load, extraction progress, and model downloads instead of text spinners.", "P4 Toasts: adopt svelte-sonner for tutorial/WASM-fallback/sync notifications, replacing ad-hoc toast implementations.", "P5 Menus & dialogs: shared Dialog/DropdownMenu wrappers that respect the app z-index scale (panels=300, NavBar=400, MergeReview=500); NavBar analyze menu first.", "P6 Button hierarchy: audit primary (teal) vs outline vs ghost usage on ingest and kb pages for consistent affordance weight.".
